  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Phrasal verbs (verb + particle): the right particle (take→off, give→up, find→out, look→up, run→out of), verb↔meaning matching, and word order — with a NOUN object either order works ('turn off the light' / 'turn the light off'), but with a PRONOUN object the particle goes AFTER ('turn it off', NOT 'turn off it'); some are inseparable ('look after', 'get on with'). 36 vocab + 70 grammar, full v1 parity (floor 40 → 70). 4 verify lenses clean after fixes (translation 0 defects). Fixed the vocab agent's mc-as-objects bug (the schema needs mc:string[], not [{text,tier}] — affected all 36 vocab items). Granted 'off' (the bare particle — taught by the SB box but absent from the bank, exactly the g4-u11 reflexive-grant pattern) + set/took/broke/gets/takes/stops/shuttle + advertisement/answer (vocab alt answers) + could/floor/nearly/finished/wrong (carrier commons the level-gloss lens surfaced). Flipped tr.004/tr.005 to lang:en (they are enToDe with English-source prompts). Reworded 5 mc prompts that were written in English under a lang:de label → proper German ('Welcher Satz hat die richtige Wortstellung mit it?' etc.). Reworded 6 jargon prompts ('Phrasal verb' / 'Verb' → functional 'Welche Bedeutung passt?' / 'Welches kleine Wort passt?' / 'durch eins wie give up / take off'). The answers lens's mc.009 second-correct-in-pool resolved on re-mint (its distractors are now all clearly wrong). 2 defensible warns (altogether → 'insgesamt / alles in allem'; the prompt 'Zieh deinen Raumanzug an!' — the 'an'/'in' homographs trip the language-evidence heuristic; both are correct German). Validate green."
